item.dc:creator: @whackatre Whackatre
item.description:
@whackatre wrote:

I’m in the unfortunate position of migrating completely into general programming and completely away from private servers (I find it fairly embarrassing to post on Moparscape especially on a pserver-related thread), but as the founder and former owner of PR I feel I have a responsibility to defend the honor of my old server. I apologize if I am veering the course of this topic too much.

[quote=“ox random xi, post:6, topic:478809”][quote author=Flame_ link=topic=597027.msg4204122#msg4204122 date=1358653519]

rainbow scape I think is pretty long, that’s the one with 400+ customs right?

Yes. Their community is quite dead right now though, last I checked.
I think the name is Project Rainbow, also.
[/quote]
Yeah it’s not supported, I’ve heard a lot of the stories of their staff being LOLZY over the long run of years.[/quote]

Except it is not quite dead. There are 35 players right now which I would consider average (well at least for a damn customs server anyway). Perhaps a little more if the server could last more than 500 minutes (haha).

[quote=“Flame_, post:7, topic:478809”]Their staff team is lazy, and from what I’ve heard, extremely corrupt.
The game itself is quite interesting though, yet it could use a neater layout of in-game, such as monsters and more boss locations.[/quote]

That might have been a direct inheritance from me and my general indolence.

If you have any questions about corruption I am more than happy to answer them either here or elsewhere in private. I understand that we have a rule about keeping server harmony and many individuals fail to recognize it, which is usually the reason for such a misinformed spreading. If you are referring to how I tend to cuss openly at players through our IRC integration (basically how I talk to players without having to log in), I apologize for my large superiority complex which can hopefully explain my occasional elitist attitude and the fact that I am easily appalled by imbecility.
